    • Method Detail

      • buildTileMap

        public void buildTileMap(java.lang.String pathToTileGraphics,
                         int[][] tileData,
                         int tileWidth,
                         int tileHeight)
        Builds your tilemap and draws graphics from pathToTileGraphics TileData must be a 2d array of integers tileWidth and tileHeight correspond to the width and height in pixels of each tile. The Tilemap's tile size must correspond with the tileWidth and tileHeight
        Parameters:
        pathToTileGraphics - Path to the tileset in the assets directory
        tileData - 2d integer array containing tile data
        tileWidth - Width of each tile in the tileset
        tileHeight - Height of each tile in the tileset

      • setTileGraphics

        public void setTileGraphics(java.lang.String path)
        Sets tileGraphic to specified path, does not change the look and feel of tiles untill the map is reloaded
        Parameters:
        path - Path to tilesheet
